description:
The greatest freedom that man can have is the freedom to think as he chooses, the freedom to appear wrong in another mans eyes without any consequence. At the heart of Gods government is free will as God does not want anyone serving him our of coercion or force and whilst freedom of worship is prevalent in many places today this chapter outlines how these freedoms will be gradually stripped away.
